Interface StringCondition

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Condition
    All Known Subinterfaces:

    public interface StringCondition
extends Condition
    A StringCondition is a Condition on string values.

      • negate

        StringCondition negate()
        Description copied from interface: Condition
        Returns the negated form of this condition.

        This also works for already negated conditions. The following statement is always true: 

         condition.getNegated().getNegated() == condition // always true
        Specified by:
        negate in interface Condition
        Returns:
        The negated condition. For already negated conditions, the regular non-negated condition will be returned.

      • applies

        boolean applies(java.lang.String text,
                java.lang.String searchValue,
                TextMatchMode matchMode)
        Applies this condition to the given text and search value, considering the given match mode.
        Parameters:
        text - The text to search in. Must not be null.
        searchValue - The character sequence to search for. Must not be null.
        matchMode - The text match mode to use. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        true if this condition applies (matches) given the parameters, otherwise false .
